<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-106-278 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 980 444</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  July 15 1991 v13 n28 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A tool to help you find a needle in the Windows haystack.andO;(Microsoft Windows 3.0 graphical user interface) (Window Manager)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Livingston, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft's Windows 3.0 graphical interface can make a system veryeasy to use, but Windows itself is complex and requires its ownset of tools to simplify work.andP;  The Windows Shopper's Guide,published by WhiteFox Communications, is a printed catalog ofWindows applications that is updated twice a year.andP;  Examples ofunusual Windows applications include Talkman, a voice-recognitionpackage that lets factory workers control a Windows applicationwithout a keyboard; Dine Windows, a dietary analysis package fromDine Systems; and McRetail, an application for small andmedium-sized retail stores that includes inventory planning, cashregister data capture and sales analysis features.andP;  The WindowsShopper's Guide lists 20 database programs and is an excellenttool for those seeking just the right application to suit theirneeds.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (Computerprograms).andO;Topic:     Graphical user interfaceBooksUtility programsFile Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>